SeriesDescription: Tourism direct GDP as a proportion of total GDP (%)
Source: Statistical Institute of Jamaica: National Income and Product
FootNote: The 2007 and 2010 the TSA Table 6 (Domestic Supply & Internal Tourism Consumption) was compiled based on  data from the Jamaica Tourist Board for Inbound Tourism Expenditure and  a Domestic Tourism Expenditure Survey. For the years when a Domestic Tourism Expenditure Survey is not done, the ratios for the domestic tourism is held based on the Supply & Use tables which are also compiled for those years. It must be noted that domestic tourism accounts for a small percentage of Tourism Direct GDP (3.9 per cent in 2019). Inbound tourism, which accounts for the majority of Tourism Direct GDP, is done for all years.
